Subject: [PATCH 210/800] sched / idle: Export cpu_idle_poll_ctrl

Export cpu_idle_poll_ctrl so that it can be used in modules.

Signed-off-by: Dave Gerlach <d-gerlach@ti.com>
[zou: Original patch taken from PROCESSOR-SDK-LINUX-AM335X 02_00_01_07]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 kernel/sched/idle.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/idle.c b/kernel/sched/idle.c
index fefcb1f..d2bbcfe 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/idle.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/idle.c
@@ -26,6 +26,7 @@ void cpu_idle_poll_ctrl(bool enable)
 		WARN_ON_ONCE(cpu_idle_force_poll < 0);
 	}
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(cpu_idle_poll_ctrl);
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_GENERIC_IDLE_POLL_SETUP
 static int __init cpu_idle_poll_setup(char *__unused)
